t the endpoints (<em>k<sub>1</sub></em> and <em>k<sub>4</sub></em>), since =
we expect these to be a better estimate of the slope when going from <em>y*=
(t=E2=82=80)</em> to <em>y*(t=E2=82=80+h)</em>.</p>
